Subject: Re: [T2] 6-rib transmission swap

On Oct 22, 2007, at 11:53 AM, Martin Jr., D. Michael wrote:

> I have an 091 6-rib transmission from a 1976 that I want to mate up  
> to a type
> 1 style motor.  I know I saw somewhere the how to's and option but  
> cannot seem
> to find them now.
>
> 1.  Can you use the existing bellhousing with the 6-rib?

You will need to use your current bell housing with the 091 body.

> 2.  Do you have to shave length off the input rod?

Use the old input shaft. Combined with the old bell housing, the end  
will sit properly in the gland nut.

> 3.  Does the nose cone need to be swapped out?

No, it's 091 specific.

